<h3>&AGENT:name; Match Criteria</h3>

<blockquote><em>
  The match criteria specify the transactions in which this agent is
  interested.  A <code>-</code> after a criterion name indicates that the
  criterion must be <em>false</em>; criteria with no value specified must be
  <em>true.</em>  <em>All</em> criteria must be met in order for the agent to
  match and its ``Act-on'' hook (below) to be executed.
</em></blockquote>

<pre><protect result='result' markup='markup'>&AGENT:criteria;</protect></pre>

<h3>&agentName; Agent Act-On Hook</h3>

<blockquote><em>
  This is the source code for the banner that <a href='/&amp;agentType/&agentName;'>&agentName;</a> puts on top of every 
  page.  It can be customized by making an edited copy of the 
  initialization document,
  <code><a href='/PIA/Agents/&agentType;/&agentName;/initialize'>/PIA/Agents/&agentType;/&agentName;/initialize.xh</a></code>,
  and putting it in your personal InterForm directory as
  <code><a href='/~/Agents/&agentType;/&agentName;/initialize'>~/.pia/Agents/&agentType;/&agentName;/initialize.xh</a></code> or
  <code><a href='/~/Agents/&agentName;/initialize'>~/.pia/Agents/&agentName;/initialize.xh</a></code>.  The latter is not as
  good because it could get confused with another agent of the same name and a
  different type.
  (Replace <code>??</code> in the names above with the current one of
  <code>xh</code> (new) or <code>if</code> (old).)
</em></blockquote>

<pre><protect result='result' markup='markup'>&AGENT:act-on;</protect>
</pre>
